1. *Ugasi* svetlo, molim te. (Turn off the light, please.)
2. Hoću da *ugasim* motor da bismo uštedeli gorivo. (I want to turn off the engine to save fuel.)
3. *Ugasili* su požar pre nego što se proširio. (They extinguished the fire before it spread.)
4. Ako ne *ugasimo* ovu epidemiju, situacija će biti još gora. (If we don't put out this epidemic, the situation will get even worse.)
5. Ne mogu da nađem daljinski za televizor da bih mogao da *ugasim* ga. (I can't find the TV remote to turn it off.)
6. *Ugasite* računalo prije nego što odete. (Turn off the computer before you leave.)
7. Da li si siguran da si *ugasila* šporet pre nego što si otišla? (Are you sure you turned off the stove before you left?)
8. *Ugasićeš* mi muziku, molim te? (Can you turn off the music for me, please?)
9. Moramo *ugasiti* tu svađu, nije zdravo za naš odnos. (We need to put an end to this argument, it's not healthy for our relationship.)
10. *Ugasila* sam sve aplikacije na telefonu da bih sačuvala bateriju. (I closed all the apps on my phone to save battery.)

Note: In the Serbian language, the word "ugasi" can mean "turn off," "put out," or "extinguish," depending on the context.